The paper deals with the characterization and optimization problems on a specific graph class, namely max point-tolerance (MPT) graphs. The graph class has applications in genome-wide association studies and telecommunications, which suggests a connection to the sub-category cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also characterizes MPT graphs as a special case of several 2D geometric intersection graphs, which suggests a connection to the sub-category cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The study of combinatorial optimization problems on MPT graphs suggests a connection to the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper demonstrates connections to several well-known graph classes, which suggests a connection to the sub-category cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
